<methods>
<methodStep>
<description>
<section>
<para>
<literalLayout>The soil of the site was classified in JAKUCS, P. (1985): Ecology of an oak forest in Hungary. Akad&#233;miai Kiad&#243;, Budapest, pp. 19&#8211;32. The original Hungarian classification was transormed to FAO WRB.

Soil samples were analysed by an accredited agrochemical laboratory according to standard Hungarian procedures.
The following parameters were measured: pH(H2O), soluble salts, upper plasticity limit, calcium-carbonate, humus, total phosporus, total inorganic  nitrogen, K2O, C%, N%, C/N.



</literalLayout>
</para>
</section>
</description>
<instrumentation>Soil samples were analysed by accredited agrochemical laboratory of Mezogazdasagi Szakszolgaltato Kft. (Hodmezovasarhely, Hungary)</instrumentation>
</methodStep>
<sampling>
<studyExtent>
<description>
<section>
<para>Soil samples were taken from the upper 20 cm in May, July and November of 2012. Samplings represent 1 ha permanent plot of the LTER site.</para>
</section>
</description>
</studyExtent>
